The paper deals with a problem that arises in shared-memory systems, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem involves data structures and algorithms for concurrent operations, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses benchmarks and performance analysis, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). The self-healing property of the algorithm involves system dynamics and control, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the reliability of other randomized implementations, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
